// PLACEHOLDER GameMaker Studio 2 extension manifest.
//
// The real .yy schema is JSON with a long list of fields including
// resource UUIDs and platform target masks. Generating it correctly
// against an evolving LTS schema is a follow-up (see PR 4 / packaging
// in the GameMaker Studio 2 plan). For now, this file documents the
// intent; users should manually create the extension in their GMS
// project per examples/gms2-extension/README.md.
//
// Once the .yy schema has been exercised against a working extension
// import, this placeholder is replaced with a verified manifest
// declaring:
//
//   - Three Proxy Files (Windows / macOS / Ubuntu) under binaries/
//   - A reference to elevator_ffi.gml + elevator_ffi_generated.gml
//   - Calling convention: dll_cdecl (default)
//   - Platform target mask for desktop x64 only
//
// Every function declaration the .yy contains is auto-generated by
// scripts/gen-gms-bindings.py reading bindings.toml's `gms` column —
// the same source the generated.gml file uses.
